Content: so is pirate a part of komodo or how does that work?

Author: ComputerGenie 👴🏼📢#7004
Content: Pirate uses the komodo platform (including komodo dPoW), but is a stand-alone chain

Author: gets#8925
Content: ok, what does it mean that it ‘uses’ the komodo platform? if u dont feel like explaining can u point me to some reading material? 😛

Author: gets#8925
Content: also greetings to whoever I was just chatting with on twitter, seemed like a cool guy 😃

Author: ComputerGenie 👴🏼📢#7004
Content: Komodo, itself, allows chains to be spawned that are not KMD but use the code of Komodo to create a new chain. The main advantage of doing this over forking the Komodo code is that this give the independent chains near-instant updates and the entire dev backing of Komodo

Author: ComputerGenie 👴🏼📢#7004
Content: among other benefits

Author: gets#8925
Content: is there a cost for that?

Author: gets#8925
Content: or how does it work if u change stuff and it breaks when komodo pushes an update?

Author: ComputerGenie 👴🏼📢#7004
Content: You can change stuff and maintain complete autonomy (like Veruscoin does) or never change anything an just update as Komodo does

Author: ComputerGenie 👴🏼📢#7004
Content: PIRATE does the latter with updates being pushed to Komodo as needed

Author: FishyGuts#5085
Content:
AFAIK the only costs under KMD are the annual dPoW costs.  
I believe you can launch a chain free of charge, yes @ComputerGenie 👴🏼📢 ?

Author: ComputerGenie 👴🏼📢#7004
Content: Yes, chains are free (in fact on an average week I spin up 20-30 new chains for testing), but dPoW does cost because it costs to operate dPoW

Author: FishyGuts#5085
Content: The KMD team and chain teams offer integration services which would be a separate cost/fee based on the services they specifically offer.

Author: FishyGuts#5085
Content:
But as an example pirate was launched free and pays for dPoW. 
We benefit from Komodo in many ways.   Dev costs and times are exponentially reduced in many cases.  Most recently, the Verus coin project implemented Sapling and has given their work to Komodo.   Now Komodo is integrating the activation date for 12/15 and after that, asset chains can adopt the new changes.   So pirate will adopt the initial sapling integration.

Author: gets#8925
Content: I see, but aren’t u then over reliant on upstream updates?

Author: FishyGuts#5085
Content: Pirate can focus on going forward with further advancements like zSPV wallet development.   Otherwise we would be working furiously to get devs to integrate Sapling still.

Author: FishyGuts#5085
Content: No. We could perform these tasks as well.

Author: gets#8925
Content: do u have a plan in place for funding if thats ever needed?

Author: FishyGuts#5085
Content: It would take time money and effort.

Author: ComputerGenie 👴🏼📢#7004
Content: sapling updates are a perfect example of why to use an assetchain over forking - all the dev, debugging, and testing is essentially done pro bono

Author: FishyGuts#5085
Content: Yes.  We have some of the mining pools designating funds from their fees.   All exchanges we get in we have a ref link we use to refer for use.  The on boarding program is probably our biggest generation of revenue.
